<div id="banner">
	<h1>you&#8217;re losing whuffie, buddy</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p><a href="http://scriptingnews.userland.com/stories/storyReader$1657">Right on</a>. The XML world gets crazier and crazier, adding complexity until nobody can understand or adopt it. </p>

<p>Watch this: <a href="http://www.craphound.com/">Cory</a>&#8217;s fellow <a href="http://boingboing.net/">BoingBoinger</a>, <a href="http://boingboing.net/markf.html">Mark Fraunfelder</a> (of <a href="http://www.apple.com/switch/ads/markfrauenfelder.html">Switch</a>), is <a href="http://www.thestandard.com/article/display/0,1151,19498,00.html">writing about Cory</a> talking about <a href="http://opencola.com/">his old company</a>. &#8220;In the novel, death, disease and poverty have been eliminated, and warring groups of Disney freaks fight for the right to maintain the rides at the original theme parks.&#8221;</p>

<p>Coming this fall: <a title="Down and Out in the Magic Kingdom, by Cory Doctorow" href="http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&amp;lr=&amp;safe=off&amp;q=%22down+and+out+in+the+magic+kingdom%22">The End of Cost</a>. <em>It&#8217;s great!</em></p>

<p>Lots of people, <a href="http://diveintomark.org/archives/rooms/30_days_to_a_more_accessible_weblog/index.html">30 days</a>.</p>

